nodes.title: Seed
nodes.summary: This is the start of the your mind map.

nodes.title: Recording
nodes.summary: The process of capturing audio or video that has just started, according to the speaker.

nodes.title: Waiting Period
nodes.summary: A specified duration of approximately thirty seconds required for a process to complete or stabilize, mentioned multiple times.

nodes.title: Demo Video
nodes.summary: A specific type of video intended for demonstration purposes, which is planned for future action.

nodes.title: Uploading

nodes.title: Next Steps
nodes.summary: Refers to the subsequent actions or plans that need to be considered or addressed after the current tasks.

nodes.title: Content Push/Post
nodes.summary: Refers to the action of making content or data available, publishing, or committing it, as implied by the phrases 'hasn't pushed anything' and 'posted it just now'.

nodes.title: JSON Data
nodes.summary: A specific data format that is mentioned and whose operational status ('seems to be working now') is currently being discussed.

nodes.title: Operational Status
nodes.summary: Indicates the current functional state of a system or component, specifically that the JSON data is now 'working', implying a resolution to a previous issue.

nodes.title: Title
nodes.summary: A label or name for content, which is noted as currently missing or needing to be defined for an upcoming video or post.

nodes.title: Video Creation
nodes.summary: The action or requirement of producing a video, explicitly stated as a task that 'we do have to make'.

nodes.title: Desk Post
nodes.summary: A specific type of content or publication, referred to as 'our desk post', that is planned to be created or published.

nodes.title: Fill Up Base
nodes.summary: A preliminary or foundational action, described as being performed 'briefly,' likely setting up an initial state or configuration.

nodes.title: Idea Verification
nodes.summary: The process of confirming or validating a proposed concept or plan, following an initial assessment that it is a 'good idea.'

nodes.title: Elevated Position
nodes.summary: Refers to one participant being situated at a slightly higher physical level, potentially for better visibility or as part of a demonstration setup.

nodes.title: Group Observation
nodes.summary: The collective action of the remaining participants moving around and intently watching a central event or demonstration.

nodes.title: Dev Post
nodes.summary: A specific type of post, likely for developers or about development, that the speaker intends to add participants to and contribute content to.

nodes.title: Content Typing
nodes.summary: The action of preparing or drafting textual content by typing, specifically referring to 'our stuff' for an upcoming post.

nodes.title: Our Content (Draft)
nodes.summary: Refers to the material or information that the speaker plans to type out and include in the 'Dev Post.'

nodes.title: Display/Retrieval Action
nodes.summary: The action of making information or data visible, often by retrieving it and showing it on an interface, as inquired by the speaker ('pull it up').

nodes.title: Current Status Check
nodes.summary: The speaker's inquiry about whether a specific action or process, such as data retrieval and display, is occurring or complete at the present moment ('Does it pull it up now?').

nodes.title: Expressed Approval
nodes.summary: The speaker's positive sentiment or satisfaction concerning something observed or confirmed, indicated by the repeated phrase 'I like that. I like that one.'

nodes.title: Continuous Update
nodes.summary: The process of an entity or system repeatedly modifying its state or data, expected to continue in the future, as indicated by 'it's gonna keep updating it'.

nodes.title: Acceptance of Consistency
nodes.summary: A verbal affirmation that the observed state or process is acceptable and aligns with previous expectations or states, indicating stability, as in 'That's fine. That's fine. It's same thing.'

nodes.title: Difficulty Acknowledgment
nodes.summary: The speaker's direct recognition or statement that a particular situation or task presents a challenge or is difficult to manage, as noted by 'that's tough'.

nodes.title: Conditional Hope
nodes.summary: An expression of optimism for a desired result, which is made conditional on a past action or decision taken by the speaker, implying some uncertainty, as heard in 'hopefully, if I did it'.

nodes.label: Two-by-Two Arrangement
nodes.summary: A suggested or observed grouping pattern, likely referring to people or items being paired, as in 'Two by two'.

nodes.label: Arrangement Setup
nodes.summary: The act of arranging or configuring elements, explicitly mentioned as 'I'll set this up' and 'We'll set it'.

nodes.label: Verbal Communication
nodes.summary: The act of speaking or conversing, referred to as 'when we're talking' and 'two people are talking'.

nodes.label: Laptop Preparedness
nodes.summary: The state or instruction for a participant to have their laptop open and ready for use during a discussion or presentation ('have your laptop up').

nodes.label: Cursor Reference
nodes.summary: A specific mention of a 'Cursor', possibly in the context of demonstrating something on a screen or pointing during a discussion.

nodes.label: Two-Person Discussion
nodes.summary: A specific scenario or suggestion involving only two individuals engaged in verbal communication ('just two people are talking').

nodes.label: Participant: Thomas
nodes.summary: A named participant in the conversation, whose suggestion is mentioned ('Thomas, like, Why don't we just bring more Email').

nodes.label: Email Involvement
nodes.summary: A suggestion or question about increasing the use or involvement of email in a process or discussion ('bring more Email').

nodes.label: Participant: Pranav
nodes.summary: A named participant from whom an email address is requested ('Pranav, what's your email?').

nodes.label: Email Address Request
nodes.summary: The explicit action of asking for a participant's email address, specifically 'Pranav, what's your email?'.
